<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[192,1440,227,347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,336,227,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Galileo &amp; Martins, 2010" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2010" box="[341,623,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Calycibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricolle" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[341,623,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Calycibidion rubricolle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[629,721,228,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Napp and Martins, 1985" authorityName="Napp and Martins" authorityYear="1985" box="[877,1330,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Calycibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turbidum">
<emphasis box="[877,1027,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C. turbidum</emphasis>
Napp and Martins, 1985
</taxonomicName>
concerning the elytral apices with two spines. It is distinguished by its black head and reddish pronotum; black antennae; black legs with coxae and femur bases reddish. The head and prothorax of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Napp and Martins" authorityYear="1985" box="[1241,1394,291,315]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Calycibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turbidum">
<emphasis box="[1241,1394,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C. turbidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are black; the pedicels, the flagellomeres and the legs are brownish.
</paragraph>
